In a victory for the reclusive writer J. D. Salinger, a federal judge on Tuesday barred publication in the United States of a a new book by a Swedish author that contains a 76-year-old version of Holden Caulfield, the protagonist of “The Catcher in the Rye.”

The judge, Deborah A. Batts of United States District Court in Manhattan, had already granted a 10-day temporary restraining order against the author, Fredrik Colting, who wrote the new novel under the pen name John David California.



